{"section": "Exercise 2.11.1: Applying the Euclidean Algorithm and the Extended Euclidean Algorithm.", "qid": 1, "instructions": null, "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   4)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   The two linear equations above can be used to express gcd(225, 60) as a linear combination of 225 and 60:\n   <br/>\n   <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n    15 = C \u00b7 225 + D \u00b7 60\n   </span>\n   <br/>\n   <br/>\n   What is the correct value for D?\n  </div>\n </div>\n <div class=\"question-container flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"input\">\n   <pre><!----><textarea class=\"zb-text-area hide-scrollbar ember-text-area ember-view\" cols=\"20\" id=\"ember108\" rows=\"1\" spellcheck=\"false\"></textarea><!----></pre>\n   <div class=\"buttons flex-row\">\n    <button class=\"check-button zb-button primary raised ember-view\" id=\"ember109\">\n     <!-- -->\n     <span class=\"title\">\n      Check\n     </span>\n    </button>\n    <button class=\"show-answer-button zb-button secondary ember-view\" id=\"ember110\" style=\"\">\n     <!-- -->\n     <span class=\"title\">\n      Show answer\n     </span>\n    </button>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </div>\n</div>\n", "choices": [], "answer": "<div class=\"answer\">\n <p>\n  81 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 60 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 21 \n\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 18  \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 3 \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 0\n </p>\n <p>\n  81 mod 60 = 21\n </p>\n <p>\n  60 mod 21 = 18\n </p>\n <p>\n  21 mod 18 = 3\n </p>\n <p>\n  18 mod 3 = 0\n </p>\n <p>\n  The equations for substitution are:\n </p>\n <p>\n  3 = 21 - (21 div 18)18 = 21 -18\n </p>\n <p>\n  18 = 60 - (60 div 21)21 = 60 - 2\u00b721\n </p>\n <p>\n  21 = 81 - (81 div 60)60 = 81 - 60\n </p>\n <p>\n  Substitute (60 - 2\u00b721) for 18 into the equation 3 =  21 -18\n </p>\n <p>\n  3 =  21 - (60 - 2\u00b721)  = 3\u00b721 - 60\n </p>\n <p>\n  Substitute (81 - 60) for 21 into the equation 3 = 3\u00b721 - 60\n </p>\n <p>\n  3 = 3\u00b7(81 - 60) - 60 = 3\u00b781 - 4\u00b760\n </p>\n <p>\n  gcd(81, 60) = 3 = 3\u00b781 - 4\u00b760\n </p>\n</div>\n", "explanation": null}